       The  _r_._o_u_t_._b_i_n  program  exports  a  GRASS raster map to a binary array
       file. Optionally, output can be sent to standard  output  (stdout)  for
       direct  input (pipe) into other applications.  Data is exported accord-
       ing to the original GRASS raster type (e.g. float). If the "-i" flag is
       specified,  an  integer  array  is  output.  The  region parameters are
       printed to stderr.

